Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.96,0:00:11.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I mean is: four, five or six.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.09,0:00:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've had six cases this month. Count 'em, six. Kudou, what about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.51,0:00:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, me?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.43,0:00:20.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've solved seven cases.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.18,0:00:22.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dang, I lose again!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.02,0:00:26.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But say, Kudou, doesn't it seem that an awful lot of cases occur around you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.11,0:00:30.86,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: The {\i1}ji{\i0} character in Heiji's name means {\i1}next{\i0} or {\i1}follows{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.11,0:00:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if your resigned to defeat, then the way you write your name suits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.19,0:00:34.03,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: The {\i1}ichi{\i0} character in Shinichi's name means {\i1}one{\i0} or {\i1}best{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.19,0:00:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm Shin-ichi; therefore, I'm number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.11,0:00:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you're number two.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.20,0:00:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Number two?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.78,0:00:41.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it happened a while ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.41,0:00:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was someone whose brain was sharper than yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.75,0:00:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.47,0:00:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Middle school detectives Heiji & Shinichi fight a deduction battle on the ski slope!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.89,0:00:59.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Will they solve the lift riding mystery?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.39,0:01:00.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.85,0:01:02.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.47,0:01:04.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.87,0:02:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This Meitantei Conan special is brought to you by P&G and by these sponsors. {Maybe Use Detective instead of Meitantei to stay consistent}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.17,0:03:00.80,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,HATTORI HEIJI vs KUDOU SHINICHI\NDEDUCTION SHOWDOWN ON THE SKI SLOPE
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.14,0:03:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha, say, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.64,0:03:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If your leg's sprained badly, shouldn't you go back to the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.86,0:03:15.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's fine, I said. Fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.78,0:03:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Being alone at the hotel would be boring. It'll be more fun to be where I can watch everyone skiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.28,0:03:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And also...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.95,0:03:26.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:32.12,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Jizou statue - Statue of the popular Buddhist deity Jizou (a bodhisattva who guards children). A common sight throughout Japan.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.70,0:03:32.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So what I thought was a homely Jizou statue sitting in the snow is really a person?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:35.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the heck's wrong with you? This is the fifth time!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.67,0:03:36.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Apologize to Kazuha now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.38,0:03:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why should I have to apologize?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.34,0:03:43.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just tossing snow on her sprain so it'll cool down and heal faster.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.35,0:03:49.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Teacher! Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is flirting with some girls again!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.73,0:03:51.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you guys say?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.19,0:03:52.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's got nothing to do with us!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.10,0:03:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The old ladies are getting angry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.90,0:03:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Old ladies?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.82,0:03:57.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.94,0:03:58.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.94,0:04:03.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Give it up and hurry back to the hotel; you'll catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.53,0:04:05.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.66,0:04:07.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are boys like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:13.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Translator's Note: Yuki-onna (Snow Woman) - A youkai (spirit) popular in Japanese folk tales who appears as a beautiful woman on snowy nights and lures travelers to their deaths.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.49,0:04:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hope the Yuki-onna of this mountain eats you for dinner!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.75,0:04:13.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yuki-onna?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.25,0:04:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The teacher told us a folklore story about these mountains called {\i1}The Legend of the Yuki-onna's Silver Gown{\i0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.05,0:04:23.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago on this very mountain, there was an extraordinarily beautiful woman who wore a silver gown that sparkled with white light
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.64,0:04:30.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She caught sight of a good man traveling by foot on the mountain and she began to beguile him with a voice like the song of a snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.97,0:04:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Will you exchange your most treasured possession for my silver gown?" she said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:42.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The foolish man was overcome with lust by the sight of the white skin beneath the gown, and so he agreed to the condition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.53,0:04:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.57,0:04:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While the man was bundling the delicate gown in a wrapping cloth, he said:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.12,0:04:52.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My only really treasured possession is this gun, but do you really want it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.21,0:04:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the woman responded from behind him:
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.75,0:04:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.25,0:04:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, do you want money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.71,0:04:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.21,0:05:01.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My hat?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.51,0:05:02.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.72,0:05:10.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, without making a sound, the woman embraced him from behind with her naked body and:
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.22,0:05:12.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not cold things like those.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.23,0:05:18.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I desperately want are the warm, warm...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.36,0:05:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...drops of blood...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.48,0:05:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,...from your heart!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.69,0:05:24.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She cried.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.95,0:05:31.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later, when they found the man's body, inside the wrapping cloth, instead of the silver gown,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.41,0:05:34.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it was said they only found a large quantity of snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.25,0:05:38.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say whenever there's a blizzard on this mountain, another victim appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:42.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems there was a new, awfully similar incident here four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.84,0:05:47.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Kaihou Academy Middle School students! Lunch!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.14,0:05:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already past two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.89,0:05:51.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:54.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No wonder I was hungry.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.39,0:05:57.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like some other school is staying at this hotel too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.19,0:06:01.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it seems they shifted the time so we wouldn't get mixed-up in the cafeteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:09.41,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, isn't that Minowa Shouhei, the actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.90,0:06:10.91,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Minowa Shouhei (32)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.39,0:06:10.91,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,What's he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.12,0:06:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah! I heard on TV they were making a movie based on an incident that really happened up on the snowy mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.75,0:06:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? I heard it was a mystery movie about the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.08,0:06:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heh, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.96,0:06:27.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, in any case, since that Minowa Shouhei guy is the lead,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.84,0:06:32.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,no matter which mysterious incident they're going for, I think he'll play the role of detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.18,0:06:35.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.97,0:06:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, I heard you'll be filming the third and concluding episode in the Yuki-onna series this time. {Maybe use Snow-Woman instead of Yuki-onna?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.23,0:06:45.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't they say it would be a motif about an actual incident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.94,0:06:47.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's correct too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.90,0:06:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased was my friend and our stuntman.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.16,0:06:52.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was there where it happened, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.45,0:06:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.41,0:06:59.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the deceased was our Mizugami Jirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} is kind of a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.37,0:07:00.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.79,0:07:04.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,People on the Internet already know we're filming something about our late friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.75,0:07:09.26,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Ooyama Morizou (56)\NMovie Director
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.75,0:07:09.26,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Hey, now. This film is being made in memory of his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.26,0:07:10.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it's OK, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.30,0:07:14.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who's dead and gone isn't going to come back and do handstands about it
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.81,0:07:18.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we say our last movie is being devoted to Mizugami Jirou,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.31,0:07:21.06,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,it might bring out the sympathy of the audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.81,0:07:21.06,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Mimata Kousuke (27)\NStuntman
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.06,0:07:23.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way the movie will be a hit or even our best.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.65,0:07:27.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should be grateful to Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}; he might make this movie a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.32,0:07:31.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so should you, after all it was due to his death that you got the job as his replacement.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.32,0:07:35.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, shouldn't you be more careful?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.78,0:07:39.50,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,After all, you're the one who has to take on the deceased Mizugami's stuntman role.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.29,0:07:40.16,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tateishi Shizuku (31)\NMake-Up Specialist
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.16,0:07:42.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be lured by the Yuki-onna, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.71,0:07:43.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.96,0:07:45.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I still don't really understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.38,0:07:49.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} go and leave a fiancée like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.05,0:07:51.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To have ended his own life...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.09,0:07:53.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.05,0:07:56.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't suicide; it was murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.35,0:08:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I figure one of you was the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.89,0:08:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that police detective again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.23,0:08:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, he's not a police detective anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.53,0:08:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was canned for putting too much time into the incident on this mountain, which was in the wrong prefecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.07,0:08:15.32,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Katashina Rikuto (35)\NPrivate Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.07,0:08:15.32,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Now I run a simple private detective business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.70,0:08:18.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But still, no matter how you look at it, he committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.91,0:08:20.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It does look that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.45,0:08:28.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four years ago, a man riding alone on the lift at this ski joint, had a bullet shot through his head by a pistol and stopped drawing breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.00,0:08:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a gun in his right hand, gunpowder residue on his cuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.13,0:08:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Considering it normally, it looked like he offed himself with the pistol, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.22,0:08:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.43,0:08:44.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why had the bag sitting on the seat beside him been packed with a large quantity of snow?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.69,0:08:50.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because he was imitating the legend of the Yuki-onna that's told in these mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.36,0:08:53.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's stupid. I've known that guy since he was a kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.95,0:08:57.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He never gave a hoot about ghost stories.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.37,0:09:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, even assuming that was true, I can't understand the reason for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.16,0:09:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we don't know how to ask a dead man, here's what I say...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.46,0:09:13.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was murder, it would be one no human could possibly have done, an impossible crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.17,0:09:20.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet, if we assume it could be done, naturally it could only have been the beautiful demon of the snowy mountain, the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.51,0:09:21.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you dumb or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.52,0:09:27.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's called a crime because a human being did it! And what's more, how could it be impossible! Idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.99,0:09:34.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone said that earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.95,0:09:38.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A boy came and objected to this story saying the same things that you just did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.82,0:09:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was a middle-school student around the same age as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.74,0:09:42.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A middle-schooler?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.25,0:09:44.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.51,0:10:00.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly. You made such a big scene in the cafeteria, someone must be making fun of you and laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.93,0:10:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! That was because you were frightened by that Yuki-onna talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.23,0:10:08.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just thought I'd wake up your sleepy-thinking head.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.06,0:10:13.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wasn't frightened! I just thought it sounded real.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.19,0:10:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuki-onna stories... There are a lot of them that are sad and feel real.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.82,0:10:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it definitely sounded mysterious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.58,0:10:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Japan's most famous Yuki-onna story, the monster is called "Woman of the Snow." Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.75,0:10:35.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,English? Doesn't the Yuki-onna come from a Japanese story?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.51,0:10:37.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's from Japanese folklore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:47.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,{\fs65}Translator's Note: Lafcadio Hearn was a writer and journalist who moved to Japan in 1890 and wrote a number of works including {\i1}Kwaidan: Stories and Studies of Strange Things{\i0}, in which the story in question is included.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.05,0:10:42.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That story was written in Japan by an English teacher; Lafcadio Hearn he was called.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.26,0:10:47.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was published in English. You've heard of Koizumi Yakumo? That was his pen name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.02,0:10:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes. Shinichi is so clever that he knows everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.77,0:10:57.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, thank you. You said those things so I wouldn't be frightened, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.82,0:11:02.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I didn't say it, I had a bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.08,0:11:07.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A premonition that this might turn into a storm.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.71,0:11:19.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Heiji. What would you do if a real Yuki-onna appeared?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.34,0:11:23.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, if there were such a woman, I'd like to meet her.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.51,0:11:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.05,0:11:29.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To solve this four-year old case, first I have to examine the lift in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.77,0:11:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I need to get ahead of that other middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.90,0:11:38.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don't need to worry about that It just means there's another person who thinks the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.65,0:11:44.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I can't lose! If he beats me, people will think I'm at a middle-schooler's level too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.41,0:11:45.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are a middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.33,0:11:48.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's the couple in love!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, it's not like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.67,0:11:55.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They say when two people trace out their love with their ski tracks, the snow will melt!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.00,0:11:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, she's talking about those other people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.46,0:12:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, if you're going to check out the lift, you'll have to come back later when this snowstorm's settled down.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.97,0:12:06.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's OK, but first...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.22,0:12:09.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.89,0:12:11.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, it was my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.94,0:12:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.69,0:12:17.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Knock it off already!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.28,0:12:20.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been watching us and filming for quite a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.36,0:12:24.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, it's OK! She's probably just filming the snow-covered scenery.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.37,0:12:29.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. This old lady's been filming me!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:31.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because she's my mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.29,0:12:40.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's my Heiji. You're perceptive instincts are just like Heizou's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, what are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.93,0:12:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji's almost never been to the north-east before, so I was worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.47,0:12:53.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be silly! She's just adding to the video collection she's making of me from when I was born all the way until I'm an adult
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.77,0:12:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I want to see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.27,0:12:58.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was a snowstorm just like this then too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:02.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On that day four years ago when Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.95,0:13:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,t feels like that day too. Were we're also waiting until we could film.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.57,0:13:09.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was surrounded by fans then also.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.83,0:13:13.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like the snowstorm is starting to settle down.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.46,0:13:15.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.75,0:13:18.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, will you let us see you ski?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.00,0:13:22.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Show us you're skiing techniques from Yuki-onna's Love and Mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.46,0:13:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.84,0:13:27.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'll be difficult We'll be starting to film now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.59,0:13:28.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.22,0:13:33.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since we got here, you fans have demanded he ski for you three times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.52,0:13:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to see him skiing, go and watch the movies!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.69,0:13:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.15,0:13:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wei I, the schedule is tight, but we have to make sacrifices for our important fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.49,0:13:46.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} have said it this way?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.11,0:13:49.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will work out somehow.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.66,0:13:53.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he's no longer here, so forget that stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.58,0:14:01.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry. Here you and Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} were going to become man and wife, and we have you involved in this movie about his death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.59,0:14:07.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I was the one who asked to participate. One way or another I feel there's something I need to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.43,0:14:11.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Some truth about his death might come out when we film this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.85,0:14:18.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two places then...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.85,0:14:19.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.15,0:14:25.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can see it from below. There are two places where the lift gets close to the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.44,0:14:28.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, could somebody have jumped on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.36,0:14:31.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it gets close, but it's still three meters difference.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.99,0:14:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'd be impossible without a trampoline.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.21,0:14:41.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that the Minowa Shouhei guy we saw at the hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.00,0:14:43.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's pretty good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.64,0:15:02.23,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore! Encore!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.48,0:14:59.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way, that was the one time for today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.77,0:15:02.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the next one, please watch the movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.86,0:15:08.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already close to four. We need to hurry and shoot the scene at the top of the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.24,0:15:12.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you ride the lift up before me. It'll be pitch black after five.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Director.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.29,0:15:19.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have you seen hide or hair of the make-up specialist girl or the stuntman?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.79,0:15:23.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, those two said they were starting up on the lift before us.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.34,0:15:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.09,0:15:30.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's definitely something about this lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.43,0:15:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Heiji. Doesn't this lift scare you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.85,0:15:38.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that, Kazuha? Since you're in the advanced class, you've been on lifts before, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.48,0:15:42.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have, but they were a different type than this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.44,0:15:47.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it starting to blow up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.07,0:15:50.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can't even see the outline of the detective guy that's riding ahead of us anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.66,0:15:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.62,0:15:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.37,0:15:58.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing on the down lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.41,0:16:00.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I kinda missed my chance to get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.75,0:16:02.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not very good with things like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.68,0:16:12.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shinichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:14.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What was that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.93,0:16:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sound of a pistol. That's what the sound was.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.52,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The director, Ooyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.18,0:16:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The actor, Minowa.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.19,0:16:24.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the detective guy. That was the order.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.56,0:16:27.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.77,0:16:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.90,0:16:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know. I was just getting off now too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.34,0:16:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop the lift!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.72,0:16:55.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Take a look and figure it out! At that!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.51,0:17:00.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just stop the lift right away! Then call the police and paramedics!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.68,0:17:02.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shinichi? Did something happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.98,0:17:04.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran, don't look!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.40,0:17:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lift's stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.36,0:17:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on? First that "bang" noise, now a scream.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.74,0:17:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lift, a gunshot Could it be that the same thing that happened four years ago is happening now?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.87,0:17:27.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We are extremely sorry for any inconvenience to our guests. Please wait a short while until lift operations are restored.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.54,0:17:30.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that mean? It's like that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.84,0:17:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.55,0:17:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r} shot himself. That day.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.93,0:17:38.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mizugami...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.05,0:17:43.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The muzzle of the gun was pressed into his temple. Bang! It's suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.10,0:17:46.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. He was holding the gun in his right hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.35,0:17:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is this bag next to the dead man.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.19,0:17:53.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have an unpleasant feeling that I know what's inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.82,0:17:55.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like I thought, it's snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.95,0:17:58.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, it's just like four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.03,0:18:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think I remember hearing that you were going to film a movie here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.50,0:18:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.62,0:18:08.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A movie relating the incident four years ago to the legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:12.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But now our lead actor, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, has ended up like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.50,0:18:14.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh, Minowa? The actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.63,0:18:17.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I'm not mistaken, you were there at the time of the incident four years ago as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.89,0:18:22.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm the movie's director, Ooyama. I was riding the lift directly in front of his.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.68,0:18:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I heard the gunshot, I was just getting off the lift
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.02,0:18:29.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That boy was the one who noticed what happened to Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.32,0:18:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, kid! What do you think you're doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.28,0:18:36.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, if we don't start the lift soon, what will we do about the customers?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.49,0:18:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, once we get the body and check for any related articles, you can start it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.41,0:18:42.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Need a hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.62,0:18:44.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's relatively light.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.75,0:18:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's slimmer than he looks, no more than 60 kilograms (132lbs).
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.92,0:18:51.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't appear in anything except winter dramas and movies.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.09,0:18:55.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said he didn't want people to see his underweight body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.93,0:19:02.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why did he have his skis behind him instead of wearing them?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.01,0:19:06.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well now, that's probably because he had to carry this bag stuffed with snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.68,0:19:11.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's full of snow now, it's big enough for a child to fit in.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.94,0:19:14.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, go ahead and start the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.78,0:19:16.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mr. Policeman!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.61,0:19:19.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are three points I'm concerned about.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.87,0:19:24.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's finally moving.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.24,0:19:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are a lot of people gathered there. I'm afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.46,0:19:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! It's making me all excited!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.50,0:19:35.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Outsiders stay back! Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.42,0:19:37.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.51,0:19:38.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it's you, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.47,0:19:44.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Roughly, according to what they said, it looks like it's the same as the case four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.68,0:19:51.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems a man riding by himself on the lift, with a bag full of snow beside him, shot himself with a gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.98,0:19:54.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if he'd been possessed by the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.82,0:19:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.69,0:19:58.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't your jurisdiction!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.99,0:20:02.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, I've quit being a police detective. I'm private now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.99,0:20:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what's more, I was riding on the lift directly behind the victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.20,0:20:10.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you have some things to ask me, Mr. Detective?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.37,0:20:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Victim?" He committed suicide!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.04,0:20:15.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's too early to decide that
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.42,0:20:18.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey, Heiji! Save me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.21,0:20:20.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you doing? Hurry and get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.76,0:20:22.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How? I don't know how to get off!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.76,0:20:27.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, when you reach the bottom the lift will stop again. Be sure to get off then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.06,0:20:28.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.64,0:20:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That idiot, that's why I told her not to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.14,0:20:35.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, there was another customer who didn't get off earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.40,0:20:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.36,0:20:40.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it was a pretty woman who had her hair tied in the back.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.11,0:20:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noway! Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} killed himself? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.41,0:20:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we wonder why, could you answer a few questions for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.91,0:20:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like why you didn't get off the lift here before.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.12,0:20:56.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I couldn't get off! I'm not good with these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.46,0:21:02.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that kinda strange? Shouldn't you have come here four years ago to film that movie?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.13,0:21:06.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That time Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} rode up with me. This time I came with Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.72,0:21:08.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's not very athletic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.64,0:21:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Didn't I hear from the director that you went up earlier?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.69,0:21:16.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How is it you were riding the lift with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.44,0:21:23.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The film crew was standing by but the director and lead actor hadn't come up yet So I skied down to call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.45,0:21:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the way I noticed her riding down on the lift, and when I called to her, the gunshot went off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.91,0:21:37.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had a strange premonition about it, and so I asked Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} to ride up on the lift with me, and that's how we came up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.67,0:21:39.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of what happened four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.00,0:21:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then the lift stopped, and we were just now able to get off.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.80,0:21:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. In other words, the director, Ooyama, who rode the lift in front of Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.47,0:21:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the detective, Katashina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who rode behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.72,0:21:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was on the down lift as it passed by,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.94,0:21:58.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was on the slope.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.27,0:22:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of you were able to shoot Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.65,0:22:03.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.82,0:22:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now! Didn't you hear what I said just now? When the gunshot went off, I was with Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.99,0:22:15.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that gunshot was a fake, then the crime becomes possible. That's what you were going to say, right, kid?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.08,0:22:17.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's it exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.25,0:22:21.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't you remember that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was holding onto the gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.55,0:22:23.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could something like that be done from a distance?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.21,0:22:28.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You aren't going to say we held onto the murder weapon after shooting him are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.14,0:22:32.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, at the time the snow was blowing pretty violently.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.35,0:22:35.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't you think it'd be impossible to shoot him without a considerable degree of skill?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.43,0:22:39.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I haven't considered all that yet, but there are some things that are suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.98,0:22:43.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all, the ski poles from the lift Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.61,0:22:48.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The circular fittings attached to the ends have been inverted on both poles.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.61,0:22:51.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's proof they were used for something.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.62,0:22:54.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The next one is the lift Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was riding.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.33,0:22:59.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the plastic on the left side of the seat, there's a place where it's been cracked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.21,0:23:02.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That could also have been used for some kind of trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.00,0:23:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the last one is the cloth bag that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had riding beside him, stuffed with snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.47,0:23:12.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't why, but it's frozen solid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.76,0:23:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop that You mustn't touch the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.22,0:23:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I must say everywhere I go nowadays there are middle-school students brimming with curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.48,0:23:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was one earlier. A middle-school student who was arrogantly pointing out the exact same three points to us policemen as you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.61,0:23:28.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.90,0:23:31.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was here just before you came.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.41,0:23:36.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm finally off. I'm never riding that lift again.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.04,0:23:38.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.87,0:23:41.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you in the advanced ski class?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.33,0:23:44.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you don't know how to get off a lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.29,0:23:45.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Confess!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.96,0:23:48.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to be in the same advanced class with Hattori, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.26,0:23:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So your sprained leg is fake too...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.59,0:23:53.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! That's not true!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.51,0:23:56.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's OK, we'll keep it a secret from Hattori.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.43,0:24:01.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Excuse me! Is there anyone here who happened to videotape Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} earlier when he was getting on the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.77,0:23:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.10,0:24:03.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're welcome to my video.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.19,0:24:06.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.19,0:24:09.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My, this is really well filmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.32,0:24:12.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I would have expected Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s fans to only follow him.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.61,0:24:19.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, my son asked me to do that He told me to film the lift boarding platform as a reference for the incident four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.41,0:24:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is your son a police detective or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.58,0:24:26.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's just a regular middle-school student It seems he wants to be a detective though.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.42,0:24:29.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective, eh? It's the same with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.84,0:24:33.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's this? Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} is busy chatting with some beautiful madame.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.30,0:24:35.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, he sure takes after someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.72,0:24:40.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, that face is his detective face. He's still a greenie.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.89,0:24:46.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, can the self-styled world's preeminent mystery writer solve this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.73,0:24:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yukiko, that's a silly question.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.32,0:24:51.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} already figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:51.99,0:24:56.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I just came here to get hints about the incident four years ago for a book I'm writing.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.12,0:25:02.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's already too late, what with that movie their filming. And then virtually the same incident occurs a second time...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.75,0:25:05.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, if you know who the criminal is, rush over and tell the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.92,0:25:09.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope, I'm going to entrust this to the youngsters and sit back and watch what develops.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.96,0:25:12.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But won't you give me a little hint?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.01,0:25:19.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know? There's another legend in these mountains about the Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.56,0:25:23.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A painful and sad tale...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.56,0:25:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? The actor, Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, committed suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.03,0:25:32.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure, Heiji!?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.86,0:25:34.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't use such a loud voice!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.28,0:25:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is still off-the-record.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.91,0:25:37.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why do I have to be quiet?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.87,0:25:39.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wei I, I'm still not sure what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.95,0:25:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For a suicide, it was suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.83,0:25:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just like a case from four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.37,0:25:47.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it really was suicide, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.08,0:25:50.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly why I need to see the video.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.92,0:25:53.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well? Did you figure something out, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.05,0:25:55.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought...
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.84,0:25:57.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was definitely murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.43,0:26:00.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, I didn't expect this video to be so popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.72,0:26:02.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Popular?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.89,0:26:06.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were some other people besides you who asked to see this video.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.94,0:26:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me it was a middle-schooler!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.11,0:26:12.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, one of them was.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.53,0:26:14.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them? You mean there were others?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.36,0:26:19.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long while before that boy, there was a dandily dressed man with a mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.70,0:26:21.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A man with a mustache?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.74,0:26:25.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Another Yuki-onna legend?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.37,0:26:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there a hint about this case in it?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.75,0:26:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Listen to the whole story before you ask questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.63,0:26:34.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A long time ago, on a snowy evening...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.72,0:26:39.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Descending from the mountain and hurrying along the road home was a man by the name of Mokichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.22,0:26:47.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Along the road, he came across a very beautiful woman with long hair dressed in a silver gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.98,0:26:51.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman gave him a friendly look and said:
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.52,0:26:55.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've injured my leg on the mountain.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.24,0:26:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I can no longer manage even a single step.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.61,0:27:01.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you please carry me to my home?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.41,0:27:09.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When Mokichi inquired where her home was, without speaking she pointed at the dark black forest where no road ran.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.67,0:27:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, the farther and farther they went, the deeper the snow became, and they never came within sight of the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.67,0:27:18.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Yamato man earnestly inquired:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.55,0:27:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Have I perhaps lost the way?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.64,0:27:23.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman nodded silently.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.26,0:27:26.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She had been waiting...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.23,0:27:28.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For the man to abandon her.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.35,0:27:30.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.69,0:27:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's true character was one who waits until a man's strength falters, and then consumes his soul: a Yuki-onna.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.20,0:27:45.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before long the man's progress started to slow, and after a long silence, his lips began to move:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.58,0:27:48.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miss...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.25,0:27:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman had been waiting and hoping for this, and with a smile she replied:
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.84,0:27:54.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.50,0:27:59.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Out of breath, in a strained voice Mokichi said:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.30,0:28:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you cold?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.14,0:28:08.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The man's unexpected question surprised the Yuki-onna and left her at a loss for words.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.48,0:28:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mokichi was numb from the cold, and afraid for his life, but nevertheless he continued:
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.94,0:28:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's uncomfortable in that basket, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.07,0:28:18.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aren't you hungry?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.11,0:28:23.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a little more patience. Hold on. Just hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.78,0:28:26.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman's only reply was "yes".
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.83,0:28:31.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Her voice gradually grew weaker, until at last he could no longer hear her.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.04,0:28:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Concerned, he stopped walking...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.00,0:28:38.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when he peered into the basket...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.59,0:28:39.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The woman had disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.59,0:28:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In her place there was only a large quantity of snow wrapped inside her silver gown.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.93,0:28:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.06,0:28:52.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The warmth of Mokichi's heart melted the Yuki-onna's cold one, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.06,0:28:54.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.10,0:28:54.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.94,0:28:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was the hint in that?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.44,0:28:59.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm. As I feared, the load was too heavy for you, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.94,0:29:03.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But for him, it might make a good practice exercise.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.36,0:29:04.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Him?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.32,0:29:11.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he's watching Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s movies at the hotel now, if he really is my son.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.62,0:29:13.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look! Just as I thought!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.83,0:29:18.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you think Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s skiing in this video is a little different from what we saw today?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.30,0:29:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? I think they're both great
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.17,0:29:22.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He's a well known professional after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.18,0:29:25.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, look!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.51,0:29:28.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This part, where Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is rescuing the heroine that fainted.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.47,0:29:33.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he's skiing down, until he goes out of frame, his cap strap... Look, it's attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.64,0:29:37.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when he comes into the frame again, when he rushes over to her, it's no longer attached.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.23,0:29:40.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though they're both in the same cut
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.11,0:29:41.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.03,0:29:42.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a double?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.82,0:29:44.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he can't really ski.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.53,0:29:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be it! Earlier he was really ripping! It was cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.28,0:29:51.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure it was him?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.04,0:29:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course I am!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.75,0:29:54.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have it on video.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.63,0:29:57.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.00,0:29:59.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Sonoko...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.46,0:30:03.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you know where Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} left his bag while he was skiing?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.26,0:30:06.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, he left it in front of his fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.97,0:30:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He said there was something important in it and asked us to watch it until he returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.87,0:30:12.47,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Souvenir Counter
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.18,0:30:12.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? This bag?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.89,0:30:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A middle-schooler came to look at it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.85,0:30:15.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When was this?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.14,0:30:19.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just a bit ago. He didn't buy one though.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.61,0:30:24.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, if that's too small for your needs, we have a larger size with the same design.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.15,0:30:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.78,0:30:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This belt can be lengthened like this; that can be very convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.91,0:30:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, it really is!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.03,0:30:31.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that convenient?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.74,0:30:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey Heiji, what are you so angry about?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.87,0:30:35.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why shouldn't I be?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.29,0:30:38.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter where I go, that middle-schooler is one step ahead of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.17,0:30:41.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He rented the video from the hotel before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.05,0:30:44.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then there's that weird guy with the mustache.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.63,0:30:47.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this keeps up, they'll solve the case before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.63,0:30:50.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean you haven't figured anything out yet, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.39,0:30:55.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I already knew who the murderer was and how they did it when we were back in the shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.89,0:30:58.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that case, shouldn't you go to the police right away?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.40,0:30:59.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it's not completely solved!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.27,0:31:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like the inverted ring on the ski poles and the frozen bag full of snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.99,0:31:08.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I can't figure those out, then my reasoning won't be complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.20,0:31:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Shizu? Didn't I tell you not to make personal calls to me while I'm working?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.41,0:31:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? A case you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.87,0:31:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.83,0:31:19.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.50,0:31:20.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.54,0:31:25.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember? Didn't we hear a sound just before the deceased Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} reached the top of the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.38,0:31:27.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A sound like a gunshot?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.38,0:31:30.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they haven't retrieved this yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.47,0:31:33.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The criminal must still be somewhere they can't get away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.76,0:31:37.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, sounds like you know everything already.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.73,0:31:42.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the crucial trick used to commit the murder still hasn't come to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.44,0:31:45.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The crack left on the lift to the left side of the corpse...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.07,0:31:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What caused that?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.82,0:31:51.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that bag of snow. Even though I know who the criminal is, I don't see how that's connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.49,0:31:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? You know who the criminal is?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.49,0:31:57.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's one of the four suspects the police are questioning now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.62,0:32:00.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who was riding the lift just before Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}: Ooyama, the director...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.25,0:32:04.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one riding just behind Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}: the detective, Katashina{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.00,0:32:08.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one on the slopes going to call the director and the others: the stuntman, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.97,0:32:11.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the one who missed getting off the lift: Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.93,0:32:18.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a second, other than the director, Ooyama, how do you know which order the other three boarded in?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.10,0:32:21.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because I told him.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.14,0:32:22.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Shinichi's mother?!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.27,0:32:28.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be in the right place to overhear when they were talking with the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.15,0:32:30.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really? But how... why?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.07,0:32:32.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a complete coincidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.41,0:32:35.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My husband's and my vacation just happened to coincide with Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s ski lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.99,0:32:37.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just happened to coincide, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.95,0:32:39.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.50,0:32:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're thirty minutes late.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.08,0:32:46.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was just here. Another middle-school boy just like Shin{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.63,0:32:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? You mean there's another middle-school detective idiot like Shinichi here? How weird!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.85,0:32:58.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of another, did you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.27,0:33:01.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's another legend about the Yuki-onna and her silver robe.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.06,0:33:04.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, it's already pitch black.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.48,0:33:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though the criminal's been held this long for police questioning, when they release them, they'll be able to hide the evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.44,0:33:11.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.65,0:33:12.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.28,0:33:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using the rain will form a puddle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.87,0:33:17.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With snow, you can make a snowman.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.91,0:33:21.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's ice, you can use it to make an enormous statue.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.04,0:33:26.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yuusaku said it was the key to solving the mystery of this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.05,0:33:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be led astray by the way things appear, Heiji. By Heizou.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.67,0:33:33.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.84,0:33:36.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What does that snowman story have to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.30,0:33:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.56,0:33:48.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can we get this over with?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.03,0:33:53.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but could you get the phone from my coat pocket?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.24,0:33:55.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who's there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.61,0:33:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're a little busy right now...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.45,0:33:59.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand it all now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.41,0:34:04.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know who murdered Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and made it appear to be a suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.75,0:34:08.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the trick the murderer used to make it possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.67,0:34:09.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I know it all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.92,0:34:12.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, that middle-school kid again.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.09,0:34:18.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So are you here to tell us again that how the four of us could have killed Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.22,0:34:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We already told you, it was impossible for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.22,0:34:24.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He was by himself on the lift, so we couldn't have placed the gun in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.98,0:34:28.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, except for the detective who's a former policeman,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.15,0:34:32.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We wouldn't have been able to aim at and shoot him in the head during that snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.90,0:34:34.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.49,0:34:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That'd be impossible for a former policeman also.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.45,0:34:40.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At any rate, in that snowstorm I could barely see his lift in front of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.70,0:34:41.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's exactly it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.12,0:34:44.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The murder would have been impossible in that situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.17,0:34:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really was...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.00,0:34:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really riding alone on the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.01,0:34:53.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.26,0:34:54.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.26,0:34:59.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not saying there was someone riding along inside the bag are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.43,0:35:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that bag was packed with snow, and an adult would be way too big to fit inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.77,0:35:08.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. They hid in this bigger bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.44,0:35:14.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They sell a larger sized version with the same design as the bag that was packed with snow at the shop in the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.36,0:35:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.49,0:35:21.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} intentionally carried a bag with the criminal in it and got on the lift with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.03,0:35:27.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the person in the bag wasn't the criminal, but Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.21,0:35:29.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noway! How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.21,0:35:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the one carrying the bag...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.29,0:35:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was the criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.92,0:35:38.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s face was mostly hidden by his hair, and he was wearing sunglasses at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:43.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was wearing a wig, a knit hat, sunglasses, and ski-wear...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.51,0:35:46.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It could easily seem like it was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.39,0:35:50.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But didn't he have a conversation with our fans?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.81,0:35:53.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They'd have no problem hearing Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.65,0:35:54.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.82,0:36:01.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} listened carefully from within the bag and replied appropriately.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.57,0:36:06.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way it wouldn't be that much of a stretch to believe the disguised criminal was Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, would it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.83,0:36:08.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.33,0:36:09.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.50,0:36:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why he didn't say anything at the time until he picked up the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.17,0:36:15.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You must be joking.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.80,0:36:19.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With his excessive pride, he'd never hide inside a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.97,0:36:21.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.26,0:36:24.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly why he hid, because of his pride.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.68,0:36:27.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Likely his professional level skiing skills...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.93,0:36:32.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were just a facade, made up for appearances. They were nothing but a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.65,0:36:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.06,0:36:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, he may have been able to ski a bit, but I don't think he was at a professional level.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.73,0:36:46.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I watched Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s ski-scenes in the movies {\i1}Yuki-onna's Love{\i0} and {\i1}Yuki-onna's Mystery{\i0} at the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.29,0:36:53.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And in the scenes where he was skiing over to the heroine, he always intentionally went out of the frame and then came back in.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.88,0:36:59.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, when he was skiing the strap on his cap was attached, but in the close-ups, it wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.46,0:37:02.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the skiing must have been done by someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.55,0:37:05.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Mr. Director?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.76,0:37:06.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.01,0:37:12.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't because he couldn't ski, but he had injured his leg during the first movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.73,0:37:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, he still insisted on doing the skiing himself, so in order to convince him we secretly put in a double.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.15,0:37:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ironically, those ski scenes were praised by the critics.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.36,0:37:27.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the second movie we used a double again so no one would notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.58,0:37:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You did?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.04,0:37:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And so, when the fans demanded it, he asked the double to ski for him and got inside the bag and waited at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.38,0:37:42.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the double came to pick-up the bag, he could appear to be holding up his end of the conversation with the fans.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.93,0:37:45.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, wait a second...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.34,0:37:48.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you saying the double was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.52,0:37:55.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one who Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} asked to take on his role and carry him around in a bag, and used that to kill him was...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.48,0:38:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stuntman, Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.40,0:38:03.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can only have been you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.65,0:38:04.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.99,0:38:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.53,0:38:12.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I think the double used in the movies was the one who died four years ago, the stuntman Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.41,0:38:16.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The skiing in the movies was different from the skiing I saw today.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.58,0:38:21.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,More than likely before Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died, he passed on the secret of the substitution to Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.13,0:38:26.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he cleverly used it on this occasion to commit the crime on the lift.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.22,0:38:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Exactly...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.39,0:38:33.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,While on the lift, he pulled Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s head from the bag, held it down, and shot a bullet through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.98,0:38:42.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He then pulled Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} out of the bag, put the gun in his hand, and jumped off holding the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.19,0:38:49.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On this lift there are two places where the height above the ground is around three meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.70,0:38:54.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the hole in the seat was made when Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.75,0:38:58.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} got onto the lift, he was sitting on the left side.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.75,0:39:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when the body was found it was sitting on the right That's proof a crime occurred.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.55,0:39:09.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be difficult for a dead person to have switch seats on the lift, wouldn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.60,0:39:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was talking with me when we heard the gunshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.60,0:39:15.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was probably the sound of a bottle rocket.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.93,0:39:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After he jumped from the lift and put on the ski-wear he'd prepared,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.19,0:39:26.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used the flame from a cigarette to light the fuse and placed it in a plastic bottle so it would launch later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.74,0:39:33.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By skiing to the bottom and talking with someone when they heard the sound, he could provide a witness for his alibi.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.04,0:39:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But where did the bag filled with snow come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.37,0:39:37.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't I just say?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.46,0:39:41.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are two places on that lift where it's only three meters to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.88,0:39:47.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could place a bag there, and then invert the ring on a ski pole and use it to hook onto it and pull it into the lift
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.26,0:39:48.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.22,0:39:49.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Three meters to the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.97,0:39:57.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ski pole is approximately 1 meter and 20 centimeters long. If you hook one strap onto the other to get more length, it might reach.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.02,0:40:00.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I wonder if you could use it to grab something during that snowstorm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.10,0:40:02.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.23,0:40:05.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You use just one ski pole, and for the remaining meter...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.86,0:40:13.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just have to lengthen the belt on the cloth bag, dampen it with water, freeze it, and it will provide the remaining meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.83,0:40:18.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ring on the other pole was inverted so that the other one wouldn't be so noticeable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.46,0:40:21.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But could he see the bag from the lift?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.71,0:40:24.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was blowing so badly you couldn't even see the lift in front of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.55,0:40:25.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.42,0:40:29.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The interval between the lifts is more than six seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.01,0:40:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The speed of the lift is around 1.5 to 2 meters per second, meaning the interval between the lifts is about 10 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.68,0:40:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if you can't see something ten meters ahead, you would be able to see a bag three meters below.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.98,0:40:46.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be even easier since he knew where the bag was.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.28,0:40:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, the evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.78,0:40:50.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.53,0:40:53.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} met Tateishi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and went with her like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.12,0:40:58.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And was detained in this lodge for questioning, he should still be wearing it
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.37,0:41:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s matching ski-wear.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.79,0:41:07.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to still have the bag Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was hidden in?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.55,0:41:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've been enduring it this whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.13,0:41:12.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's been pretty hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.09,0:41:15.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,M-Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.72,0:41:17.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it was you after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.27,0:41:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You noticed it too, Director?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.14,0:41:20.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.31,0:41:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At first I thought he'd just got better at skiing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.48,0:41:28.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I saw his body, I realized it must have been you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.78,0:41:29.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, why?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.78,0:41:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it to avenge the man who would have been your husband, Mizugami{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-senpai{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.78,0:41:39.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Four years ago, Minowa used this same trick to kill him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.50,0:41:42.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.33,0:41:48.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Remember, that day four years ago when Minowa was surrounded by demanding fans? Didn't he say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.46,0:41:55.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"It will work out somehow." He planned to transport Minowa secretly inside a bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.09,0:41:59.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Minowa took advantage of his good will and killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.06,0:42:03.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because he said he wanted to quit being a stuntman and become an actor.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.60,0:42:07.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When I shoved the gun in front of him, he finally admitted it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.77,0:42:10.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy, how could I let him become an actor?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.82,0:42:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we came into conflict, he'd expose me!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.82,0:42:16.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what I scared out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.87,0:42:22.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's ironic that the movie you were making matches this revenge plot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.62,0:42:27.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is I suspected Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was the criminal four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.63,0:42:29.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I decided to make this movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.46,0:42:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a secret until now, but the criminal in the movie was the detective that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} was playing...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.22,0:42:39.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the trick was the same one Mimata{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} mentioned from four years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.35,0:42:45.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought he might give himself up when he saw the script.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.56,0:42:48.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even though I'm no longer a police detective...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.23,0:42:53.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wish if you knew that much, that you would have stopped this senseless murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.61,0:42:59.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Revenge just calls for more revenge, and the feeling of achievement fades quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.70,0:43:02.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a snowflake in the palm of your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.46,0:43:11.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, well continue this down at the station.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.75,0:43:13.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would you come along as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.96,0:43:15.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.13,0:43:17.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do I do about this other middle-school student on the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:18.18,0:43:23.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His deduction was exactly the same as this kid's; he said everything over the phone at about the same time too.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.23,0:43:30.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Heiji, why didn't you go with the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.81,0:43:35.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, didn't I say someone would carry you down to the hotel? Fool.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.70,0:43:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only solved the thing about freezing the belt on the bag because of Dad's hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.78,0:43:45.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That middle-schooler was able to solve it all by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.12,0:43:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.08,0:43:49.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.42,0:43:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just have to take the plastic bottle and say you solved the case, so shouldn't you go see them?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.84,0:44:03.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to hear the story from Dad about the Yuki-onna pretending her leg was injured and getting into the basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.35,0:44:08.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until then, I didn't realize Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was just pretending to be good at skiing and got into the bag himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.48,0:44:11.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But you did all the deduction yourself, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.65,0:44:15.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that other middle-schooler was the one who solved the case by himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.07,0:44:17.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.40,0:44:18.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.28,0:44:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Be quiet.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:19.45,0:44:21.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even with a sprain, you had to scamper around with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.24,0:44:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to show off by getting into the advanced ski class, but you overdid it while practicing and sprained your leg, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.58,0:44:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, thanks to you showing off, I knew that Minowa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was the one in the bag right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.92,0:44:36.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you helped me out this time, I'll let it slide.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.55,0:44:37.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.67,0:44:42.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason I practiced so much wasn't to show off.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.68,0:44:47.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why are there two different Yuki-onna stories?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.89,0:44:50.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's because mothers tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.85,0:44:57.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The original Yuki-onna legend was used to caution people not to go out during snowstorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.53,0:45:06.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When they tell the stories to their children, they sympathize with the Yuki-onna, and little by little they change the way they tell them.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.95,0:45:11.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the original story where making the exchange for the silver gown leads to death,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.04,0:45:16.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,is changed into the story where she returns to the snow without taking his soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.05,0:45:21.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why there are a lot of Yuki-onna stories that are sad and seem real.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.27,0:45:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I couldn't see very well through the snow...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.56,0:45:32.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was him.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.94,0:45:34.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other middle-schooler.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.56,0:45:37.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, even though we didn't meet, we're both detectives...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.48,0:45:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well meet again someday, upon the stage of mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.83,0:47:16.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's how it was! And then that super smart detective left without even giving the police his name.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.92,0:47:20.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Isn't he a lot different than some other detective was before he was shrunk?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.79,0:47:22.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't he was so cool and modest?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.59,0:47:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But that was me...
